   <body>
      <context>
         <p>Follow this procedure to install the floor burners:</p>
      </context>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>Tools Required: Wire brush.</p>
            <p>Use a wire brush to remove any debris from the mating surfaces.<ul>
                  <li>Remove the old gasket, and discard it.</li>
                  <li>Verify there is no debris between the melter and the burner flanges.</li>
                  <li>Unhook the sparger tube safety cable.</li>
                  <li>Remove the sparger tube and clean out any debris from inside the burner. </li>
               </ul>
               <p>
                  <fig id="fig_cpp_4ff_vcc">
                     <image href="media/image1.jpg"
                            placement="break"
                            id="image_dpp_4ff_vcc"
                            align="center"/>
                  </fig>
               </p>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Inspect the burner for physical damage and wear. This includes but is not limited
               to:</p>
            <p>
               <ul>
                  <li>Cracked or dented burners may require replacement.</li>
                  <li>Look for evidence of moisture to find small cracks.</li>
                  <li>Burners with metal contamination must be replaced.</li>
                  <li>Inspect for erosion on the inside and outside of the burner tip.</li>
                  <li>The burner wall thickness is 2.1 mm (0.083 inch).</li>
               </ul>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Install a new Teflon ferrule on the sparger tube.</p>
            <p>
               <ul>
                  <li>The tapered end of the ferrule must point towards the burner tip. </li>
               </ul>
               <note type="note" id="note_bxg_gjf_vcc">
                  <p>Replace the Teflon ferrule every time the sparger tube is installed. </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <ol id="substeps_w1t_rff_vcc">
               <li>
                  <p>Tools Required: Adjustable wrench, sparger height tool (SCM1-5-7, with
                     41.3 mm (1-5/8 inch) tall setting).</p>
                  <p>Insert the sparger tube into the burner.<ul id="ul_w5n_xff_vcc">
                        <li>Place the height tool on a flat surface.</li>
                        <li>Place the burner on top of the height tool.</li>
                        <li>Insert the sparger tube until it contacts the height tool.</li>
                        <li>Tighten the nut to secure the sparger tube.</li>
                        <li>Remove the sparger height tool.</li>
                        <li>Install the safety cable.</li>
                        <li>Insert the burner plug. </li>
                     </ul>
                     <p>Torque: 80 Nm (59 ft-lb)</p>
                     <note type="note" id="note_x5n_xff_vcc">
                        <p>Handle the burner by the stem. </p>
                     </note>
                     <ul id="ul_s4d_bgf_vcc">
                        <li>Do not hold the burner by the sparger tube. Safety cables must be
                           installed to prevent the sparger tube from sliding out. </li>
                     </ul>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_y5n_xff_vcc">
                           <image href="media/image2.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_z5n_xff_vcc"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_avn_xff_vcc">
                           <image href="media/image3.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_bvn_xff_vcc"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Place a new gasket on the burner flange.</p>
            <p>
               <note type="note">
                  <p>Replace the burner gasket every time the burner is installed. </p>
               </note>
               <p>
                  <fig id="fig_m5d_khf_vcc">
                     <image href="media/image4.jpg"
                            placement="break"
                            id="image_n5d_khf_vcc"
                            align="center"/>
                  </fig>
               </p>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <note id="note_ch1_mhf_vcc">
               <table id="table_z1r_mhf_vcc">
                  <tgroup cols="3">
                     <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="1*"/>
                     <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="1*"/>
                     <colspec colname="c3" colnum="3" colwidth="1*"/>
                     <tbody>
                        <row>
                           <entry/>
                           <entry/>
                           <entry/>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                           <entry/>
                           <entry/>
                           <entry/>
                        </row>
                     </tbody>
                  </tgroup>
               </table>
            </note>
            <note id="note_jds_s5t_xcc">
               <table id="table_hln_t5t_xcc">
                  <tgroup cols="2">
                     <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="1*"/>
                     <colspec colname="newCol2" colnum="2" colwidth="1*"/>
                     <tbody>
                        <row>
                           <entry morerows="1"/>
                           <entry>
                              <p>PPE Required: Cut-resistant gloves.</p>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                           <entry>
                              <p>Tools Required: Socket wrench.</p>
                           </entry>
                        </row>
                     </tbody>
                  </tgroup>
               </table>
            </note>
            <p/>
            <ol id="substeps_y4r_phf_vcc">
               <li>
                  <note id="note_jsp_qhf_vcc">
                     <table id="table_ksp_qhf_vcc">
                        <tgroup cols="2">
                           <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="1*"/>
                           <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="1*"/>
                           <tbody>
                              <row>
                                 <entry/>
                                 <entry>
                                    <p>Caution: Burners are heavy.</p>
                                 </entry>
                              </row>
                           </tbody>
                        </tgroup>
                     </table>
                  </note>
                  <p>Lift and insert the burner into the burner port.</p>
                  <p>
                     <ul>
                        <li>Verify that the burner gasket is flush with the mating surface.</li>
                        <li>Align the burner with the bolt holes.</li>
                        <li>Tighten the bolts using a star pattern.</li>
                        <li>Complete the pattern three times, at 30%, 70% and 100% of the desired
                           torque.</li>
                     </ul>
                     <p>Torque: 150 Nm (110.6 ft-lb)</p>
                     <note type="note" id="note_zlv_whf_vcc">
                        <p>Handle the burner by the stem. <ul id="ul_czz_xhf_vcc">
                              <li>Do not hold the burner by the sparger tube. </li>
                           </ul>
                        </p>
                     </note>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_s1m_f3f_vcc">
                           <image href="media/image5.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_t1m_f3f_vcc"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>Connnect the gas, oxygen, and cooling water lines.</p>
                  <p>
                     <ul id="ul_avm_33f_vcc">
                        <li>Inspect the gaskets for damage. Replace if necessary.</li>
                        <li>Ensure the connectors are fully engaged.</li>
                     </ul>
                     <note type="note" id="note_hbv_j3f_vcc">
                        <p> Verify that lines are connected correctly using the installed tags.</p>
                     </note>
                     <p>
                        <fig id="fig_ud2_l3f_vcc">
                           <image href="media/image6.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_vd2_l3f_vcc"
                                  align="center"/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </p>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>In DFC, go to the Melter Cooling H3C screen and click the <uicontrol>Burner
                  Skid</uicontrol> tab.</p>
            <p>
               <ul>
                  <li>Click the <uicontrol>BNRx-WTR-FL</uicontrol> button.</li>
                  <li>Click the <uicontrol>Alarming</uicontrol> tab.</li>
                  <li>Uncheck the <uicontrol>Shelved</uicontrol> checkbox to enable the cooling
                     water alarm. </li>
               </ul>
               <p>
                  <fig id="fig_d33_p3f_vcc">
                     <image href="media/image7.jpg"
                            placement="break"
                            id="image_e33_p3f_vcc"
                            align="center"/>
                  </fig>
               </p>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Go to the Melter Cooling H3C screen and click the <uicontrol>Main
                  Overview</uicontrol> tab.</p>
            <p>
               <ul>
                  <li>Confirm that each burner has sufficient water flow.</li>
                  <li>Burner water flow should be greater than 2.0 m<sup>3</sup>/hr (8.8 gpm).</li>
                  <li>Turn on the burner cooling water pumps at the local disconnects. </li>
               </ul>
               <p>
                  <fig id="fig_x2v_t3f_vcc">
                     <image href="media/image8.jpg"
                            placement="break"
                            id="image_y2v_t3f_vcc"
                            align="center"/>
                  </fig>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <fig id="fig_fjw_53f_vcc">
                     <image href="media/image9.jpg"
                            placement="break"
                            id="image_gjw_53f_vcc"
                            align="center"/>
                  </fig>
               </p>
            </p>
            <ol id="substeps_h3d_w3f_vcc">
               <li>
                  <p>If there is no cooling water flow to a specific burner</p>
                  <p>
                     <ul id="ul_vnr_y3f_vcc">
                        <li>Verify that each cooling water shutoff valve is open.</li>
                     </ul>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <p>If cooling water flow to all burners is low:</p>
                  <p>
                     <ul id="ul_up2_cjf_vcc">
                        <li>Verify proper operation of the closed circuit cooling system.</li>
                        <li>The closed circuit cooling water filter may be clogged.</li>
                     </ul>
                  </p>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </li>
      </ol>
